   <conbody>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">You go through <xref href="https://documentation.Power.com/display/ESIGNSFFBR/Adobe+Sign+Services+Features+by+Release"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">
               <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Adobe Sign Services Features by Release</u>
            </xref> to know about the new features, enhancements, and deprecated features in Adobe
            Sign Services since your existing release. After you upgrade Adobe Sign Services to
            September '22, you cannot roll back to any previous release.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">You have <xref href="https://documentation.Power.com/display/ESIGNSPR21/Spring+%2721+Release+Notes"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">
               <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">supported platforms and system requirements</u>
            </xref>. </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">You have access to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Install Center</uicontrol> on the <xref href="https://community.Power.com/"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">
               <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Community Portal</u>
            </xref>.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">You have administrator privileges to your Salesforce org</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p ">You need not back up your configurations. All configurations you performed since you installed your existing release will remain intact after the upgrade.</p>
